A2A Protocol Specification — pinned reference
================================================

Source:        https://github.com/a2aproject/A2A
Docs:          https://a2a-protocol.org
Governance:    The Linux Foundation (originally developed by Google, donated
               to the LF Agentic AI ecosystem). The repository moved from
               github.com/google-a2a/A2A to github.com/a2aproject/A2A.
Spec status:   v1.0.1 (released 2026-05-28). v1.0.0 (2026-03-12) was the first
               stable major release and introduced breaking changes vs. the
               0.x preview line (spec refactor, standardized enum formats).
Pin policy:    This implementation tracks the spec at the version referenced
               below. The pin is updated only between phase boundaries, never
               mid-phase, so behaviour stays stable while a phase is in flight.

Pinned version: v1.0.1
Pinned commit:  TBD — fill in the exact tag/commit SHA at the start of Phase 1
                once the wire types are first transcribed into Go.

Reference SDK:  An official Go SDK now exists under the a2aproject org and may
                be consulted as a reference implementation for the wire types.

Scope of compliance for AgentMesh:
  - Agent Card discovery (/.well-known/agent.json)
  - Task lifecycle: created, working, input-required, completed, failed, canceled
  - Message exchange within a Task (multi-turn)
  - Artifact outputs (typed)
  - SSE streaming for task status updates

Out of scope for the v1 retrofit (see DESIGN.md §5.4):
  - A2A authentication (Bearer, API key, OAuth) — Phase 2 security layer
  - mTLS (added to the spec in v0.3.0) — Phase 2 security layer
  - Push notifications via webhook — SSE is sufficient
  - Durable task state persistence — sidecar memory only
